originalText.text:
I am absolutely not surprised that Josh has only 5 star reviews. I honestly don't know what I can add to all of the glowing reviews already on here that he so rightly deserves. My biggest concerns when working with anyone are communication, flexibility, and comfort. Right out of the gate Josh scheduled a phone consult with me to discuss needs, and continued to be available via text until our shoot date, even though he told me he would be out of town. I had initially chosen a rather soon date for the shoot and Josh let me know that he would be ready for it but that if I changed my mind we could schedule for a date a little further out if that would make me more comfortable. All three big concerns taken care of on our first phone call.

I am not the easiest person to get to look good on photos, but the shoot itself was so smooth and relaxed that I did not feel self-conscious or nervous at all. Josh showed me some of the photos as we progressed and I was shocked at how good they were. I was also a little shocked at how good I felt about myself in them.

I will absolutely be back when I need new shots and will recommend Josh whenever I hear someone say they need new shots!

originalText.text:
How do I give Josh 10/5 stars? He made our wedding day more magical than we thought possible. We had a very quick timeline, which he was able to accommodate, and he made every piece of the photography process easy to understand and fun! From the consultation, the follow-up e-mails with our "shot list," and then the day of, Josh was encouraging, professional, and made everything feel so easy and relaxed!
I cannot speak more highly of his talent, his flexibility & patience (he even took time to get some "family" shots with our very energetic pup!), and his kindness - he went above and beyond to make us and our family feel comfortable while capturing the most beautiful photos of our special day.
